  "texts": [
    "Using the comprehensive Erdős benchmark (Guo et al. 2025), we evaluate fine-tuned (G1) and non-fine-tuned open-weight LLMs, from smaller Qwen models (Bai et al.",
    "2023) to larger gpt-oss models (OpenAI 2025).",
    "We measure output and performance variability across node permutations, reorderings in the edge encoding, and textual format variations.",
    "Finally, we introduce a new suite of spectral reasoning tasks, providing additional evaluation of LLMs on graph tasks beyond purely combinatorial reasoning.We find that fine-tuning does not consistently enhance generalization on unseen, non-combinatorial tasks, while it improves robustness to node relabeling.",
    "At the same time, it increases sensitivity to internal ordering and formatting, whereas larger (non-fine-tuned) models show greater robustness."
  ],
